receipes_liked:
""RATED
  Visited this place recently for a team dinner. We we're approx. 30 people but we could not get a one table for all of us hence we had to split between veg n non veg.
Interior is really good. Nice theme they have thought of. Loved the pirates hat and few of the statue s where you can take pictures n all.
Service was also good. We were asked so many times on how's the food quality n if we want to make any changes on how the starters are getting prepared etc. We we're very much comfortable with the hospitality.
Let's come to food now. Food was I would say average as a vegetarian if I say. Not sure about the non veg. I felt they should have more better options for veg starters and also more tasty. For main course we just had Jeera Rice. No Biryani ?? which was very strange. Never expected. Desert as pretty good.
Overall good place to visit once only for team dinner and if company is paying for it. ?"")

name: Louise Ashby
receipes_liked: 'RATED\n  One of the few restaurants in Bangalore that serves great Afghani food! The Irani murgh tikka was absolutely delicious! Melt in the mouth and with a generous topping of cheese. We had ordered the Murgh Peshawari for main course along with Kabuli naan and ulte tawae ka paratha. The main course was very flavourful and the chicken pieces were unbelievably soft. Both the paratha and naan was soft and went great with the chicken. Kabuli naan was topped with dry fruits and nuts! The mugh malai tikka was a bit dry and could have been better. Phirni sweetened the meal and left us wanting more..\noverall a great meal and prompt service from the staff too.')

name: Marilyn Bergman
receipes_liked: 'RATED\n  If you wanna feel nostalgic and explore your schooling days with good food then this is that place. The ambiance is really amazing which brings out the child in you. First we got the orange ice candy which I used to love in my childhood. The we had the golden basket which was a crispy assorted veggies in a plate. The veg burger was good but the patty was only based on mashed potatoes. Thai curry with rice was amazing which was served in a tiffin box which it look so unique. I just loved the mojitos here especially the watermelon and the peach flavoured ones. They also have a wide variety of freak shakes which are wholesome and quite delicious. I would definitely recommend this place mainly for the ambiance and the flavoursome food. They also have a couple of indoor board games to play with while your food arrives.')

name: Tony Levin
receipes_liked:
""RATED
  Day 2 in Bengaluru and I couldn't leave without having some beer! Brew Meister in Jayanagar looked inviting and dropped by for a quick lunch and some beer guzzling.
It's a large and spacious space with a lot of seating. JP helped us with our orders.
Unfortunately they didn't have the stout that I wanted so I went for my favorite Belgian Wit beer. I was impressed with the beer. Called only for starters and we went for the pepper mutton and the blazing Naga pork. Both the dishes were well cooked and did justice to JP's warning of them being spicy. Portions served were generous. Spicy food lovers must try them out.
Called for a chocolate mousse cake pastry for dessert and it looked so delicious that we gobbled it down without remembering to click a picture
